    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1455"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1455">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 612.002/90.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The Spanish Minister in Mexico
                    telegraphs me that railway communication between Veracruz and the capital having
                    been cut by order of General Carranza, grave fears are entertained by several
                    foreign importers for the safe arrival to the capital of a large consignment of
                    merchandise which is now in transit.</p>
                <p>These goods are valued at 10,000,000 pesos, and they belong half of them to
                    Spanish firms and the other half to English and French importers, and most of
                    them originate from this country.</p>
                <p>I venture to request, in order to prevent the loss of this valuable merchandise,
                    that you employ your good offices with General Carranza in order to obtain a
                    guarantee for its safe arrival at the capital.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
